codex
Implemented the PHP address book app with:

- User registration, login, logout
- Per-user contact CRUD
- Contact fields: name, email, phone, address
- Name search
- SQLite database auto-created at `data/address_book.sqlite`
- `composer.json` with a `composer serve` script for port `5033`
- Short local run instructions in `README.md`

Files added: `composer.json`, `README.md`, `public/index.php`, `public/styles.css`.

I did not run or test the app because the provided working agreement says to only create source files.
diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..4757eab3fd0573b385d894cbc94b80b291e94dba
--- /dev/null
+++ b/README.md
@@ -0,0 +1,31 @@
+# PHP Address Book
+
+A small PHP address book where logged-in users can add, edit, delete, and search their own contacts.
+
+## Requirements
+
+- PHP 8.1 or newer
+- SQLite PDO extension enabled
+- Composer
+
+## Run Locally
+
+Install dependencies:
+
+```bash
+composer install
+```
+
+Start the app on port 5033:
+
+```bash
+composer serve
+```
+
+Then open:
+
+```text
+http://localhost:5033
+```
+
+The SQLite database is created automatically at `data/address_book.sqlite` the first time the app runs.
